<br>
What you call  punishment I call that the natural consequences of voluntarily placing yourself in a situation where you are unable to produce children of your own.<br>
<br>
That's a choice gay couples make and no one forces them to make it.  What's wrong is taking a lifestyle that is clearly against the natural order and then demanding the exact same consideration as everyone else.<br>
<br>
There's nothing any one can say that will change my mind on this.  Homosexuality is wrong, condoning it is wrong, forcing it upon an adopted child is wrong, and trying to convince society that you deserve the exact same benefits and then some is even more wrong.<br>
<br>
You can rationalize and justify until you are blue in the face but the fact remains that if gay couples were supposed to have children then the human body would be able to reproduce no matter what gender your partner is.<br>
<br>
